myeloma (MM) still lack reliable predictive ability to select subsets of 
patients for different therapies, in particular for intensive treatment 
protocols. In this work we aimed to test the prognostic value of the MM 
Prognostic Index (MMPI), developed in 1996 by Grignani et al. from Pavia 
University as a clinical and investigational tool.
DESIGN AND METHODS: Ninety-three MM patients were eligible for the study. All 
received initial induction therapy based on a standard 6-month melphalan + 
prednisone (M + P) protocol. Clinical and laboratory parameters, conventional 
staging and bone marrow infiltration percentage and cytopathology (BMIC) were 
assessed at diagnosis, while treatment response (TR) was evaluated using 
criteria after induction therapy. Cox's multivariate survival analysis was 
applied on prognostic data.
