POPULATION: All deaths occurring after the 50th birthday in Switzerland between 
1969 and 1994 (n = 1,390,362).
MAIN RESULTS: Age at death is increasing at a sustained rate at all percentiles 
equal or greater than 50, without any slow down in the trend during this period. 
The increase is more marked among women. Rates of increase are diminishing as 
the percentiles of age at death are higher, suggesting some clustering of deaths 
beyond the median value. However, the maximum age at death, if any, seems to be 
far from the current median values, even for women who enjoy a relatively high 
median age at death.

